@spec tm_tail_gating_spec  src=tests/specs/tm_tail_gating_spec.lua  loc=90  sha=285f562  cases=3
@exercises midiManager (h.fm), dataStore (h.ds), trackerManager (h.tm)
@surface   fm:dump, ds:assign, tm:fromLogical, tm:rebuild, fm:setLength, fm:length, tm:setLength
@harness   mk{seed.length, seed.notes}

# Intent
  Pins the tail-clip gate (design/archive/dirty-channels.md § Scheme) against its two dirt sources:
  swing reseat and take-length resize. See docs/trackerManager.md § Derivation dirt, § Length operations.

# Helpers
  @fn noteByPitch(notes, pitch)  @ 9-11

# Cases
  @case 'swing change reseats an open tail through the dirtyChans gate'  [harness]  @ 15-40
  @case 'external take-length grow re-derives tails on channels with no edits'  [harness]  @ 44-64
  @case 'setLength shrink clips an OPEN tail without concreting its endppqL'  [harness]  @ 68-88

# Uses (outbound edges)
